  <part>
    <title>Common</title>
    <preface id="intro">
      <title>Introduction</title>
      <para>PHPurple is the libpurple php binding, which makes the use of the instant
			messaging  protocols such AIM (ICQ, Oscar), MSN, Yahoo etc. within php possible.
			Learn more about the libpurple at <ulink url="http://developer.pidgin.im/wiki/WhatIsLibpurple"><citetitle>http://developer.pidgin.im/wiki/WhatIsLibpurple</citetitle></ulink>.
			libpurple docs can be found at <ulink url="http://developer.pidgin.im/doxygen/dev/html/files.html"><citetitle>
			http://developer.pidgin.im/doxygen/dev/html/files.html</citetitle></ulink>
		</para>
    </preface>
    <chapter id="requirements">
      <title>Requirements</title>
	  <para>
		First of all, you need PHP >=5.2.0, which is known as minimal compatible (please drop a mail, if you've successfully compiled on some earlier 5.x version). Actually the extension is being developed on the php version 5.2.5.
		PHPurple requilres the libpurple >= 2.2.1 and GLib >= 2.0 installed on your system as shared library. Also the pcre php extension should be compiled in (which is usually the case).
	  </para>
    </chapter>
    <chapter id="installation">
      <title>Installation</title>
	  <para>
		  If you compile the libpurple from scratch, you could use the following configure options:
	  </para>
  <para><code>user@host~# ./configure --enable-gnutls=yes --enable-nss=no --disable-gtkui --disable-consoleui --disable-screensaver --disable-sm --without-x --prefix=/usr</code></para>
<para>This will compile only libpurple. Otherwise, if you have already pidgin installed, the libpurple is normally present in the /usr/lib or /usr/local/lib.</para>
<para></para>
<para>While within PHPurple dir, invoke:</para>
<para><code> user@host~# phpize &amp;&amp; ./configure --enable-purple &amp;&amp; make &amp;&amp; make install</code></para>
<para>Since the extension is installed, you can simply add a line in your php.ini with which it'll be loaded by default. An other way would be to use the dl() php function at the top of your script</para>
<example><programlisting>&lt;?php
	if(!extension_loaded('purple')) {
		dl('purple.' . PHP_SHLIB_SUFFIX);
	}
?&gt;</programlisting></example>
    </chapter>
